    "recap_headline": "University of Houston Athletics",
    "recap_text": "LAWRENCE, Kansas \u2013\nDespite rallying for its sixth double-digit run total of the year, Houston Baseball fell to Kansas, 12-10, in game one of the weekend series on Friday night at Hoglund Ballpark.\nFreshman\nConnor Udland\n(1-1) received the loss for the Cougars (12-9, 1-3 Big 12) after tossing 4.1 innings in relief while striking out six. Throwing the last 3.1 innings for Kansas (13-8, 2-2 Big 12), Boede Rahe (4-0) claimed the win, allowing one run on four hits and walking three.\nPLAYER HIGHLIGHTS\nTre Broussard\n: 2-5, 2B, RBI, 2 R, BB\nXavier Perez\n: 2-4, HR, 2 RBI, 2 R, BB, HBP\nAntonelli Savattere\n: 2-4, 3 RBI, BB, SB\nTyler Cox\n: 1-3, 2B, 2 RBI, BB, SH\nNOTABLES\nHouston drew 10 walks in the game, its most since picking up 11 against Lamar on April 22, 2025.\nUdland recorded a career-high six strikeouts.\nJunior\nTre Broussard\nearned his 40\nth\ncareer multi-hit game.\nThe three hour, 49 minute game was Houston's longest of the season.\nGAME SUMMARY\nThe Cougars started the game with a bang, plating four runs in the top of the first and forcing the Jayhawk starter from the game. Sophomore\nMcClane Helton\nled off with a walk and scored as Broussard doubled to left center. Broussard would come home on a single from junior\nEaston Winfield\nwhile redshirt sophomore\nXavier Perez\nand Winfield scored as senior\nAntonelli Savattere\nsingled to right field.\nKansas used a solo homer to get on the board in the bottom of the first, but the Cougars piled more runs on in the third. Savattere picked up his third RBI of the game as he drove home Winfield and freshman\nBlake Fields\npushed the lead to five as he scored on a sacrifice squeeze from senior\nTyler Cox\n.\nThe Jayhawks turned the tables with a six-spot in the bottom of the third to take a 7-6 lead and added three more runs in the fourth to push its edge to four.\nHouston answered in the sixth. Perez hit his fifth homer of the season, a two-run shot to right field that also drove home Broussard to cut the deficit to 10-8. Fields doubled home junior\nRiley Jackson\nlater in the inning to further shrink the gap, setting up the Cougars to tie the game in the eighth as Cox slipped a double down the left-field line to plate Fields.\nKansas ultimately claimed the 12-10 win as Tyson LeBlanc hit a two-run homer to right field to reestablish the Jayhawk lead.\nUP NEXT\nHouston continues its three-game series at Kansas with a 2 p.m. Saturday rematch.\nSUPPORT THE COUGARS\nFans can make a direct impact on the success of Houston Baseball by\nproviding NIL opportunities\nand by\njoining the Dugout Club\nwhich provides financial support directly to Houston Baseball for needs beyond its operating budget.\nSTAY CONNECTED\nFans can receive updates by following\n@UHCougarBB\non X, formerly known as Twitter, and catch up with the latest news and notes on the team by clicking LIKE on the team's Facebook page at\nHouston Cougar Baseball\n. Fans can also follow the team on Instagram at\n@uhcougarbb\n.\n\u2013 UHCougars.com \u2013",
